<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-20T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5426</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-20T16:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2213. Referring to my despatch of May 4, 5410,<note n="1" xml:id="d33fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_817">p.
                                    817</ref>.</note> relative to the various French committees
                                blockade. I have just received from the Minister of Foreign Affairs
                                a note expressing the hope that the Federal Government would
                                designate a representative to the Permanent International Committee
                                of Economic Action.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>